<HEADLINE> HKSAR Athletes to Participate in World Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Athletes of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) will participate in
world-class games for the first time later this month, it was
announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At a special ceremony here today, the Hong Kong Post-Secondary
Colleges Athletic Association announced the formation of the SAR
team for the 19th World University Games slated for August 19-31
in Sicily, Italy.
</P>
<P>
The 30 athlete team will participate in six events, namely
athletics, swimming, diving, basketball, tennis and gymnastics.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR team will leave here on August 17 for Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
