<HEADLINE> Azerbaijian Oil, Gas Products Fall Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A total of 5.2 million tons of
oil and 3.5 billion cubic meters of natural gas were producted by
the State Oil Company of the Azerbaijian Republic (SOCAR) in the
first seven months of 1997. The gas's production represents a drop
of 3.3 percent compared with the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here Wednesday from Baku,
Capital of Azerbaijan, since the start of the year, the country's
Caspian offshore fields have produced 4.3 million tons of oil
and 3.4 billion cubic meters of natural gas, meeting plan targets.
</P>
<P>
Deliveries of crude oil for refining totaled 5.1 million
tons, down 1.1 percent from the same period last year; for gas
the corresponding figure was 2.9 billion cubic meters, 7.8 percent
less.
</P>
<P>
Overall, SOCAR drilled 85,500 meters, 18.5 percent less than
planned but 12.8 percent more than in the same period last year.
In the January-July period it drilled 39,000 meters at offshore
sites and 46,500 on land.
</P>
<P>
It said that in 1996, Azerbaijan produced 9.1 million tons of
oil and 6.3 billion cubic meters of natural gas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
