<HEADLINE> Jayasinghe Sets New Women's 200m Asian Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Susanthika Jayasinghe of Sri Lanka set
a new Asian record in the women's 200 meters first round with a time
of 22.44 seconds here today at the 6th World Athletics Championships.
</P>
<P>
The previous record was 22.53 set by China's Du Xiujie two years
ago. Jayasinghe's personal best before the race was 22.95.
</P>
<P>
China's Li Xuemei also ran a 22.44 in the last group of the round,
equaling Jayasinghe's minute-long record. 
</P>
