<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkish Fighters Bombard Rebel Camps </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Turkish fighters today bombarded
the camps and bases of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK)
in northern Iraq, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the Turkish army had launched air raids
on five PKK camps which were recently set up in northern Iraq
and the PKK had suffered great losses during the air operation.
</P>
<P>
However, the agency did not give details of the PKK losses
following the air raids by the Turkish air force this morning.
</P>
<P>
The operation was the first reported use of air power against
PKK rebels since a cross-border offensive in northern Iraq was
launched to crack down on rebel bases there in May.
</P>
<P>
The agency also said that the Turkish security forces launched
attacks on Herekol and Kato mountainous areas in Hakkari
province near the Iraqi border.
</P>
<P>
More than 27,000 people, including PKK militants, civilians
and government troops, have been killed in conflicts since the
PKK started a separatist war for autonomy in eastern and
southeastern Turkey in August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
