<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0019 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain to Host International Conference on Nazi Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The British government announced
here this afternoon that it would host an international conference
this December in an effort to resolve problems about millions of
dollars of gold seized by the Nazis during the Second World War.
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said in a statement issued
today that the conference, which is expected to attract delegates
from 25 countries, would take place in London from 2 to 4 December
to look into the question of compensation for individual victims
of Nazi persecution.
</P>
<P>
"I am pleased to say that we and our U.S. and French partners
in the Tripartite Gold Commission have agreed that the
International Conference on Nazi Gold will take place in London,"
Cook said.
</P>
<P>
"The (British) government shares the concern of the
international community about the origins and disposal of Nazi
gold," Cook said, adding "I hope that the London conference will
pool international knowledge and reach conclusions on this
important issue."
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Tripartite Commission has always
maintained that all of the gold it is holding was looted from the
central banks of countries occupied by the Nazis.
</P>
<P>
But Jewish groups have argued that between five and 10 percent
of the Nazi gold belonged to private individuals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
