<HEADLINE> Road Accidents Kill Six in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and two
others seriously injured today in two separate traffic accidents
on the Athens-Thessaloniki motorway north of Larissa, central
Greece.
</P>
<P>
The first accident took place at the 90th kilometer of the
Larissa-Thessaloniki motorway when a car carrying three young
Greeks crashed, killing all of them.
</P>
<P>
Local police reportedly attributed the accident to excessive
speed.
</P>
<P>
In the second accident, three people died and two were
seriously injured when a Mercedes with Belgian license plates
carrying five Turkish passengers ran off the road and crashed into
a pitch. 
