<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guerroui Wins Men's 1,500m World Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Hicham El Guerroui of Morocco hit the
front with 600 meters to go to win the men's 1,500 meters final with a
time of three minutes and 35.83 seconds at the 6th World Athletics
Championships here today.
</P>
<P>
Fermin Cacho of Spain kicked over world record holder Noureddine
Morceli of Algeria on the final stretch to win the silver in 3:36.63.
Reyes Estevez, also from Spain, nipped Morceli at the line for the
bronze in 3:37.26. Morceli finished a disappointed fourth in 3:37.37.
</P>
<P>
Guerroui, world silver medallist who keeps the year's best of
3:29.30, followed the early rabbit after two laps. Morceli stayed at
the fifth and didn't make his move until the last 500 meters.
</P>
<P>
Guerroui changed gear at the bell with Morceli chasing second and
Cacho third.
</P>
<P>
Cacho, a little-known runner in the world, opened a big kick on the
final curve and caught up with Morceli to everyone's surprise. The
three times world champion Algerian had no strength left at the end,
nipped by Estevez at the line. It was Moceli's first major failure
in the important meets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
