<BODY>
<HEADLINE> London Becomes 14th Most Expensive City in World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- London, the UK capital, moved up
14 places to have become the 14th most expensive city in the
world, according to a latest cost-of-living survey of 150 cities
all over the world, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Citing the twice-yearly survey by the Corporate Resources Group
(CRG), a Geneva-based consultancy firm, press reports said that
the strength of the pound and high housing costs appear to be the
main reasons for London's high jump.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that despite the depreciation of the Japanese
yen, Tokyo remains the world's most expensive city.
</P>
<P>
Moscow and St Petersburg are the only two European cities in
the top 10, ranking the third and 10th respectively. The others
are all in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong is second, Osaka fourth, and Beijing fifth, followed
by Shanghai, Seoul, Singapore and Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
The strength of the dollar drove New York up the list from 38th
to 31st. However, it still ranks below such places as Paris,
Cairo, Rio de Janeiro, Buenos Aires, Hanoi, Tel Aviv and Kiev.
</P>
<P>
The survey uses a basket of more than 200 items, including
rents, food, clothing, beverages, household supplies and
equipment, leisure and entertainment, etc. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
