<HEADLINE> Kabila Concludes First Visit to Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- President Laurent Kabila of the
Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) today ended his first visit to
Angola and returned home.
</P>
<P>
In a joint communique issued at the end of his visit which
started on Tuesday, the two sides hailed the visit as opening a
new chapter in the history of their bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
According to the communique, President Kabila and President
Jose Eduardo dos Santos of Angola held discussions and exchanged
views on their domestic affairs and international issues of
common interest.
</P>
<P>
They focused their discussions on situation in the African
continent, especially the political situation in central Africa,
said the communique.
</P>
<P>
It added that the two presidents welcomed efforts made by
international community, particularly the United Nations and the
Organization of African Unity, to solve problems in Africa.
</P>
<P>
They also hailed the recent establishment of the African
Economic Community, believing that it will help the economic,
scientific and technological development of African countries.
</P>
<P>
During Kabila's visit, Angola and the Democratic Republic of
Congo also signed cooperation accords in the fields of petroleum,
mines, education, health, culture, transport and others to
promote development and peace in the two countries. 
</P>
