<HEADLINE> Security Council Urges Restoration of Democratically </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Security Council of
the United Nations today issued a presidential statement, calling
upon the military junta in Sierra Leone to take immediate steps to
restore the democratically elected government of President Ahmad
Tejan Kabbah.
</P>
<P>
Expressing its deep concern about the situation in the country,
which endangered peace, security and stability in the whole
region, the Security Council condemned the overthrow of the
democratically elected government and underlined the need to
implement the Abidjan Agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council expressed its appreciation to the
Committee of Four Foreign Ministers of the Economic Community of
West African States (ECOWAS) for their efforts to negotiate with
the representatives of the military junta on a peaceful resolution
to the crisis and reiterated its support for the objectives of
this mediation.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council also called upon the junta to renounce its
declared intention to remain in power and to resume negotiation
with ECOWAS Committee of Four Foreign Ministers without delay.
</P>
<P>
Urging the military junta to cease all interference with the
delivery of humanitarian assistance to the people of Sierra Leone,
the Council condemned the continuing violence and threats of
violence by the junta towards the civilian people, foreign
nationals and personnel of the ECOWAS monitoring group.
</P>
<P>
The Council also expressed its concern at the effects of the
continuing influx of refugees into neighboring countries due to
the crisis in the country. It called upon all states and relevant
international organizations to provide help to these countries in
dealing with the problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
