<HEADLINE> Arafat: Palestinians Should Be Prepared for Big </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian President Yasser
Arafat today called on the Palestinian people to prepare
carefully for a big battle with Israel, believing that the
hardline Israeli government is bent on burying the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Arafat issued the call in a statement released by the Palestine
News Agency Wafa in Gaza. He told the people to prepare themselves
and plan each stage of the forthcoming struggle.
</P>
<P>
Observers here said Arafat appears to be growing more and more
disillusioned about the peace process as a result of the
intransigent policies of the rightwing Israeli government and
particularly the harsh security measures taken following the
double suicide bombings in Jewish west Jerusalem last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The suicide bombings killed 13 Israeli civilians and wounded
170 others.
</P>
<P>
The statement came amid reports in the Gaza Strip and West Bank
saying the strangling measures imposed by the Israeli government
are beginning to bite.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of thousands of Palestinian laborers who worked in
Israel before the total closure, remain at home. Also causing
economic destruction is the internal closure, under which the
Israeli troops and a net of roadblocks have prevented the
Palestinians from traveling within the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
As the economic life in the major West Bank cities depend on
contacts with villages in the surrounding area, once the link is
cut off commercial activity is virtually at a standstill.
</P>
<P>
On top of this, the Israeli decision to withhold tax revenue
collected from the Palestinian workers, to the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA), has caused the PNA to sustain a
critical shortage of funds.
</P>
<P>
Consequently tens of thousands of Palestinians employed by PNA
may not receive their salaries.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian officials and Arab leaders have sounded an alarming
bell that the Israeli hardline government is deliberately
undermining the position of Arafat and the Palestine Liberation
Organization.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian Finance Minister Mohammed Nashashibi accused Israel
of refusing to transfer 145 million U.S. dollars it owes to the
PNA. He observed that the Israel action is leading to an economic
and social earthquake in Palestine.
</P>
<P>
However, he warned, this will also boomerang against
Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
