<HEADLINE> Uganda Launches Campaign Against Cattle Diseases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A national immunization campaign
against cattle diseases of rinderpest and bovine pleuropneumonia
(CBPP) started today throughout Uganda, Radio Uganda reported.
</P>
<P>
Kezimbira Muyingo, minister of state for agriculture, animal
husbandry and fisheries, was quoted as asking the public to
present all cattle above six-month-old for vaccination.
</P>
<P>
Two injections should be given to each of the 5.3 million
cattle in the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
Only 100 shillings (about 10 U.S. Cents) will be charged for
each animal for two injections, and the vaccination campaign will
last two months, Muyingo noted.
</P>
<P>
Rinderpest is an infectious virus disease which affects cattle
and wild game like buffalos, while CBPP affects the lungs of the
animal. The two diseases are highly infectious killer diseases.
</P>
</TEXT>
