<HEADLINE> Sudan Denies Aiding Ugandan Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, August 6 (Xinhua) -- The Sudan today denied press
reports that it is providing assistance to Ugandan opposition
forces, describing them as completely unfounded.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to newsmen, Minister of Information and Sudanese
government spokesman Al Tayeb Ibrahim Mohammed Khier said the
reports were made up within the framework of Uganda's relentless
escalation of hostility towards the Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Khier pointed out that the Sudan was committed to the
agreements signed with Uganda to cease information campaigns and
to move towards a settlement of bilateral differences through
dialog.
</P>
<P>
The Sudanese-Ugandan relations are undergoing a state of
tension whereby each is accusing the other of supporting their
respective opposition forces across their common borders.
</P>
<P>
Iran has endeavoured to mediate between the two parties, but
seemed to have failed in making progress. 
</P>
