<HEADLINE> ASEAN to Discuss Election of New Cambodian Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) will discuss Ung Huot's election as
Cambodia's first prime minister to replace the ousted Norodom
Ranariddh at a special meeting on Monday.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN Secretary-General Ajit Singh said today the meeting in
Singapore would be attended only by foreign ministers from
Indonesia, the Philippines and Thailand, who have been attempting
to mediate in the political crisis in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Singh was speaking at the launch of "Private Sector Salute to
ASEAN", sponsored by the ASEAN Chambers of Commerce and Industry
to celebrate the grouping's 30th birthday on August 8.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's National Assembly on Wednesday approved the
nomination of Foreign Minister Ung Huot as new first prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia was expected to formally join ASEAN last month, but
its admission was suspended in the wake of the political crisis
which saw Second Prime Minister Hun Sen oust his rival Ranariddh
on July 6 afte fighting between troops loyal to both men.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar,
the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. 
</P>
