<HEADLINE> Major Events Since Last Party National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Xinhua New Agency today released
the first part of a retrospective article by the CPC Central
Committee Party Literature Research Center covering the major
events which have taken place since the Party's 14th National
Congress in October 1992.
</P>
<P>
In accompanying editor's notes, Xinhua says that Deng
Xiaoping's tour of south China and the Party's 14th National
Congress propelled the nation into a new historical period of
reform, opening and modernization.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, China has maintained social stability
by holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics, adhering to all
aspects of the Party's basic line, balancing relations between the
reform, development and stability, and accelerating development.
</P>
<P>
This has in turn enabled the nation to record tremendous
achievements in economic growth, the enhancement of ethical and
cultural progress, national defense, science and technology, as
well as in promotion of democracy and the introduction of a legal
system, national reunification and foreign affairs.
</P>
<P>
"China has risen to a great new height in terms of social
productivity, comprehensive national strength and people's living
standards," according to the editor's notes. "Facts prove the
correctness of the Party's line adopted during the 14th National
Congress."
</P>
<P>
The notes stressed the necessity for reviewing the glorious
historical process since the the 14th Congress in order to ensure
that all Party members join people of all ethnic groups in working
harder to score even greater achievements to greet the
convocation of the forthcoming 15th Party's National Congress.
