<HEADLINE> Algerian President Emphasizes Determination to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Algerian President Liamine
Zeroual reaffirmed here today that the Algerian government would
focus its efforts on fighting terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Zeroual made the remarks in a speech read out for him by
Minister of the Interior Mustapha Benmasour at the opening of an
African symposium on terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Zeroual said in the speech that terrorism is the most
dangerous challenge threatening humanity at the close of this
century.
</P>
<P>
"Africa is suffering the most dangerous forms of criminality
in addition to the scourge of underdevelopment. Terrorism and
other crimes related to it are real pests threatening the unity
and stability of African countries," he added.
</P>
<P>
The president emphasized that Algeria is seeking to honor its
obligatiopns toward Africa and would relentlessly try to work out
joint anti-terrorism strategies with other African countries.
</P>
<P>
Islamic militants have been waging a war against the Algerian
government since 1992 when the govenrment canceled elections that
the Islamic Salvation Front was believed to win. More than 60,000
people have been killed in the five years of insurgency.
</P>
