<HEADLINE> HKSAR Government Confident in Housing Programs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) Tung Chee Hwa said today
that the government is confident in providing enough residential
houses over the scheduled period.
</P>
<P>
Despite heavy rain this afternoon, Tung visited three
residential districts in East Kowloon to see the on-going house
redevelopment programs there. During the visit he met provisional
district board members and community leaders to hear their ideas.
</P>
<P>
"I always pay great attention to civil welfare, and housing is
currently the most important work of the government," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said public opinions about the housing issue have been
highly valued by the government.
</P>
<P>
"The government will make concerted efforts to firmly carry out
various house development programs, so that the target of
providing 85,000 units annually can be achieved and residents can
buy their own houses at reasonable prices," he stated.
</P>
<P>
He added that the ultimate goal of the government is to provide
an opportunity for every public-house family to buy their own
houses. 
</P>
