<HEADLINE> Russian Customs Face Tide of Currency Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Russian customs officers today
uncovered 106,000 U.S. dollars in undeclared currency aboard the
Professor Vize motor ship bound for Turkey, Itar-Tass reported.
</P>
<P>
The customs bureau said it suspected the ship was involved in
currency smuggling as the owner of the money was not on board.
</P>
<P>
Currency smuggling is rife in Russia. An Azeri citizen was
found trying to smuggle 13,200 dollars out of Sheremetyevo airport
in Moscow today while a Russian leaving for Finland was detained
with 18,000 dollars by customs officers, in the western Russian
city of Vygorg. 
</P>
