ASEAN Foreign Ministers meeting of 11 August 1997."
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's National Assembly voted to appoint the FUNCINPEC
party's Ung Huot as first prime minister, replacing the party's
previous First Prime Minister Norodom Ranariddh, who was ousted by
his rival, Second Prime Minister Hun Sen on July 6 after fighting
between troops loyal to the two men.
</P>
<P>
The National Assembly also voted to strip the prince of his
legal immunity on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a secret ballot, out of 99 members present in the 120-seat
assembly, 86 voted in favor of Ung Huot's nomination. 
