<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sporting Cristal Draws with Cruzeiro </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Peru's Sporting Cristal played to a
goaless draw with Brazil's Cruzeiro in the first leg of the final
of South America's premier club competition, the Libertadores Cup
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The giant-killing Cristal harried from the outset, with
strikers Julinho and Bonnet running tirelessly but failing to make
much headway against the more highly-rated Brazilian club's cool
defence.
</P>
<P>
Cheered by a capacity 45,000 home crowd at Lima's National
Stadium, the Peruvians almost took the lead in a last-minute
goalmouth scramble.
</P>
<P>
But it was Cruzeiro who cut out the best chances in fast breaks
from the back, forcing several dramatic one-on-one saves from
Cristal goalkeeper Julio Cesar Balerio.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the Libertadores Cup will represent South America
in the Intercontinental Cup against Germany's Borussia Dortmund,
winners of the European Cup.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Installs Offshore Communications Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 7 (Xinhua) -- China has installed an offshore
communications network to aid ships in distress.
</P>
<P>
The network enables onshore facilities and vessels within a
range of 50 nautical miles to receive SOS signals. It can also
provide the exact location of endangered vessels and facilitate
related rescue operations.
</P>
<P>
Facilities in Liaoning, Hebei, Jiangsu and Fujian provinces,
and Tianjin and Shanghai municipalities are currently linked to
the network.
</P>
<P>
Accidents involving fishing vessels account for over 60 percent
of China's total maritime accidents, with small- to medium-sized
vessels accounting for approximate 90 percent of the former
figure. Some 100 Chinese fishermen are killed in maritime
accidents each year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
