<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Steel Production Continues to Grow, Up 23 Percent in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Germany's steel production
registered double-digit increase in July, continuing the sector's
strong improvement this year, the Federal Statistics Office said
today.
</P>
<P>
Crude steel output reached 3.7 million tonnes in July, up 22.7
percent over the level a year earlier. Pig iron output rose 17
percent to 2.6 million tonnes.
</P>
<P>
In the seven-month period through July, Germany's crude steel
output totaled 25.7 million tonnes, an increase of 14 percent over
the same period of 1996, while pig iron output reached 17.6
million tonnes, up 12.1 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
