<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ajunwa Looks Good, Jones Seems Pale in Women's Long Jump </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Chioma Ajunwa of
Nigeria looked set to beat big names in the women's long jump when she
produced a year's world best of 7.01 meters in the qualifying round
here today at the 6th World Athletics Championships.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian got the longest leap of the round on her second
attempt, proving that her Olympic victory last year was no fluke.
</P>
<P>
Marion Jones of the United States, the newly-crowned world fastest
woman and a favourite for the long jump title, seemed rather soft in
the qualifying. The 100m world champion scraped in with a 6.59m jump,
the poorest distance among the top 12.
</P>
<P>
Another American legand Jackie Joyner-Kersee, the world champion in
1987 and 1991, qualified in equal 10th position with a 6.62m attempt.
The world heptathlon champion Sabine Braun of Germany, whose best jump
was 6.76 this year, didn't make it to the final, only managing 6.20.
</P>
<P>
However, Heike Drechsler of Germany, the 1992 Olympic champion and
world title winner in 1983 and 1993, was in a better form. She jumped
6.80 on her second outing, good enough to enter Saturday's final.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Illegal Immigrants in HK Return Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- A group of 102 Vietnamese
migrants and illegal immigrants returned to Hanoi, Vietnam, today
on the 109th flight under the Orderly Repatriation Program (ORP).
</P>
<P>
All of the returnees, comprising 97 men and five women, are
from North Vietnam, according to the Government Information
Services of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Most of them arrived in Hong Kong this year and the rest in
1996.
</P>
<P>
The group has brought to 10,945 the total number repatriated on
ORP flights since November 1991.
</P>
<P>
There are now about 3,300 Vietnamese migrants and illegal
immigrants in Hong Kong.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
