<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mubarak Meets Jordanian Crown Prince </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
and visiting Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan held talks today on the
latest developments on the Palestinian-Israeli arena, the Egyptian
MENA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
During their talks in Egypt's port city of Alexandria, they
also discussed Egyptian and Jordanian efforts to mediate the
resumption of the peace process and easing of the sufferings of
the Palestinians following the suicide Jerusalem bombings.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa, Presidential Cabinet
chief Zakareya Azmi and Presidential political advisor Osama
el-Baz attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian crown prince was accompanied by Prime Minister
Abdul-Salam Majali and Foreign Minister Fayez Tarawneh. He held
talks on Wednesday with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu,
but failed to pursuade him to ease restrictions on Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Jordan and Egypt are reportedly working with the U.S. to
formulate an initiative which might be the basis for the
resumption of the stalled peace talks ahead of a visit by
U.S. Mideast peace envoy Dennis Ross to the region on the weekend
to defuse growing tension.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian-Israeli peace talks which had been deadlocked since
Israel's construction of a new Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem
in March suffered another fatal blow when the deadly Jerusalem
bombings claimed 15 lives on July 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
