<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment in Northeast China's Province Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The inflow of overseas
investment in northeast China's Jilin Province had amounted to
6.27 billion US dollars by June, setting up more than 3,000
overseas-invested enterprises locally.
</P>
<P>
The province has economic cooperation with some 150 countries
and regions, a remarkable increase over the former figure, and
this gives a big boost to local economic development.
</P>
<P>
Nearly two-thirds of the overseas spendings, or some 2.28
billion US dollars, are involved in industrial projects. And the
majority of the remainder is invested on local agriculture,
telecoms and transportation sectors.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, local overseas-funded businesses generated more than
10.07 billion yuan in output value and yielded 1.03 billion yuan
in pre-tax profits. The enterprises provided more than 100,000
people with new job opportunities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0141 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Railway to Open Ahead of Opening of HK New Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Airport Chairman Wong
Po-yan has expressed his confidence that the airport railway could
be completed in April next year, two months ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
This would bring the railway's completion forward to the
opening of the airport at Chek Lap Kok, South China Morning Post
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's new airport is due to open next April while the
airport railway is scheduled to be completed in June.
</P>
<P>
Wong's remarks are in response to the doubts raised over
whether the airport could open on time, due to problems in the
construction of a cargo terminal.
</P>
<P>
He said the airport and the cargo terminal would be ready on
time.
</P>
<P>
The cargo terminal at the new airport is to be run by Hong Kong
Air Cargo Terminals Limited with a smaller cargo terminal run by a
German consortium.  
</P>
</TEXT>
