<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sydney Olympics Beach Volleyball Site Decided </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Bondi Beach will host the 2000
Olympic Games beach volleyball tournament, according to the
organizers on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Bondi Beach is one of the world's most famous surf
spots. "Bondi is an Australian icon, it's a location that is
recognised internationally," Michael Knight, Olympic Games
minister in the New South Wales government, said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Organising Committee for the Olympic Games (SOCOG),
the Olympic Co-ordination Authority (OCA) and the local Waverley
Council voted Wednesday night for Bondi Beach over nearby Coogee
Beach.
</P>
<P>
"If it hadn't been Bondi, people internationally would have
been quite surprised," said Knight, who is also SOCOG president.
</P>
<P>
Beach volleyball, which became an Olympic sport at the 1996
Atlanta Games, will be staged from September 16-27, 2000 with 84
men and women competing.
</P>
<P>
Matches will be staged in a four hectare secure area embracing
part of the beach and the ocean-front pavilion.
</P>
<P>
A 10,000-seat stadium and eight warm-up courts are to be
constructed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
