<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
decline on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times
Industrials Index fell by 5.38 points to close at 1953.24 points
today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume shrank to 179.59 million units, valued at
681.15 million Singapore dollars (about 466.54 million U.S.
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 267 to 81, while 263
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was again the most actively traded stock as
it registered a turnover of 20.99 million units. It was followed
by the Overseas Union Bank (OUB) Foreign which had 5.6 million
shares traded. Jardine Matheson Holdings (JMH) 400 was next with
5.46 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
BMT 100 led the gainers of the day as it rose by six dollars to
finish at 96 Singapore dollars. GE Life gained 1.3 dollars to end
at 19.5 Singapore dollars. Local computer sound card maker
Creative 50 closed 70 cents higher at 33.6 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign was
the biggest loser as it declined by 1.6 Singapore dollars to end
at 27.2 dollars. The United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign fell by 80
cents to close at 14.4 Singapore dollars, while the Development
Bank of Singapore (DBS) and the Overseas Chinese Banking
Corporation (OCBC) Foreign lost 70 cents each to finish at 18.1
and 13.7 Singapore dollars respectively.  
