<HEADLINE> Northwest China Promotes Traditional Chinese Medicine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, August 8 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi Province
has made an effort to develop research, education, and practice of
traditional Chinese medicine in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi has many natural resources useful for traditional
Chinese medicine.
</P>
<P>
It has more than 21,000 researchers engaged in traditional
Chinese medicine and medical technology who have developed
acupuncture treatments and more than 20 new medicines from Chinese
medicinal herbs useful for treating malignant tumors,
cardiovascular diseases, and digestive system disorders.
</P>
<P>
The province has set up 124 institutes and hospitals of Chinese
medicine, and more than 30 special departments and traditional
Chinese medicine clinics.  
