<HEADLINE> China Has Record Turnover in Forex Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign exchange
turnover reached a record-high of 7.365 billion US dollars in July.
</P>
<P>
The amount translated into a daily average of 335 million US
dollars, up 9.8 percent over the previous month.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume included 6.92 billion US dollars, 2.936
billion Hong Kong dollars, and 7.685 billion Japanese yen.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the Chinese yuan against the greenback and
the Hong Kong dollar remained relatively stable, but weakened
against the Japanese yen by 2.234 points last month to 7.0145
yen. 
</P>
