<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Mexican Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Tomur Dawamat, vice-chairman of
the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee,
met with Mexican Senator Gustavo Carvajal Moreno, and his party
here today.
</P>
<P>
Tomur said the exchanges between China and Mexico date back to
ancient times, and the people of the two countries enjoy
time-honored friendship, adding that the friendly cooperation in
various fields has been expanding since the forging of diplomatic
ties 25 years ago.
</P>
<P>
"The exchange of visits between the leaders of both countries
has facilitated increasing bilateral relations and promoting the
friendship between the two peoples," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the Chinese NPC and Mexican parliament
have had close contacts and sound cooperation, and that there have
been frequent exchanges between them.
</P>
<P>
Tomur expressed his thanks for Carvajal's efforts at enhancing
cooperation between parliaments of the two countries and his
consistent adherence to the "one China" policy.
</P>
<P>
Carvajal, who is also vice-president of the Inter-Parliamentary
Union, said that since Mexico and China share much in common, they
should further increase their cooperation. He expressed the hope
that bilateral ties will continue to grow.
</P>
<P>
The host and guests also conferred on other issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Mexican Ambassador to China Luis Wybo Alfaro was among those
attending the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican visitors arrived here Wednesday at the invitation
of the NPC Foreign Affairs Committee. 
</P>
