<HEADLINE> Europe Continent Sets Up Office in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- France's Europe Continent, which
is involved in commercial trade, investment, and industrial
business, has set up its first Chinese office in Kunming, the
capital of Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
The province is in a comparatively economically-backward area
that is rich in plants and mineral ore and close to Southeast
Asia, which encouraged Europe Continent to open its first
representative office there, according to Arnaud Quetin, the
company's chief representative in China.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan is one of the provinces that have had the fastest
economic development in the country, he added.
</P>
<P>
Europe Continent plans to spend five billion yuan (602.4
million U.S. dollars) on market development in the province,
promoting medical facilities, food processing and packaging
machines, and facilities for biochemical testing.
</P>
<P>
The corporation now has nine representative offices in Asian
countries, including Thailand, Malaysia, Vietnam, Cambodia,
Myanmar and Laos. 
</P>
