<HEADLINE> China to Purchase Equipment For Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The company in charge of the
construction of the Three Gorges Project has decided to purchase
the best equipment and choose the best maintenance service groups
through market competition so as to guarantee construction speed
and the quality of the Project.
</P>
<P>
The China Yangtze Three Gorges Project Development Company
(CYTGPDC) plans to encourage contractors to rent equipment in a
bid to raise the utilization rate of the machines.
</P>
<P>
The CYTGPDC has held several rounds of domestic or
international bidding since the project started and has bought
more than one billion yuan worth of equipment.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the value of the equipment needed in the
whole project will come to about 70 billion yuan (about 8.75
billion US dollars), or nearly one third of the project's overall
investment.
</P>
<P>
After the damming of the Yangtze River at the end of this year,
the project will enter a key period, during which the largest
amount of equipment is needed and the biggest power generating set
in the world will be installed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
