<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Develop Chain Store Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Internal Trade
has worked out an ambitious plan on the development of chain
stores in China.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, China will set up three chain-store
enterprises with an annual sales volume of over one billion yuan
each, 50 chain-store firms with a yearly sales volume of over 100
million yuan each and 30 chain-store companies possessing over 50
shops each.
</P>
<P>
China will also establish several large trans-regional
chain-store groups.
</P>
<P>
Minister Chen Bangzhu said at a recent meeting that
chain-stores have developed quickly in China these years and have
brought about obvious economic and social benefits.
</P>
<P>
Chain-store development hereafter will be focused on expanding
the scale and improving management, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chain stores started to develop in China in the early 1990's,
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, by the end of 1996, there
were more than 700 chain-store enterprises in the country, with
over 10,000 shops.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, chain stores accounted for 1.2 percent of the total
turnover of the retailers in the country.
</P>
<P>
A survey shows that the prices of goods for daily use sold in
chain stores are five percent lower than in department stores.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Airport Industrial Zone Reports Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Tianzhu Airport Industrial
Zone beside the Capital International Airport has reported steady
growth since it was established three years ago.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 projects with a total investment of 375 million US
dollars have been started in the zone. Overseas-funded businesses
account for 60 percent of the projects, and five of them have an
investment of some 50 million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
The 1.96-sq-m-zone is installed with water supply, sewage
disposal, power and heat supply, telecommunications, and transport
facilities. Moreover, it has a customhouse, and a public bonded
warehouse.
</P>
<P>
Some projects in the zone cater especially for the nearby
airport. The biggest of them is the 70-million-US-dollar
CASC-Airbus Training and Service Center, which is also the largest
project in the Asia-Pacific Region by the European consortium
Airbus Industrie.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, five of the 30 projects became operational, yielding
an output value of 450 million yuan (54 million US dollars). This
year 15 to 18 businesses are expected to go into operation,
producing a total output value from 1.5 to two billion yuan (181
to 241 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Experts said that the zone will focus on hi-tech, high
value-added and low-pollution industries with more foreign
currency returns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
