<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Link Up in Action Against Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
engaged in Operation Jaya Sikuru against Tamil rebels achieved
another objective Wednesday by linking up with the troops
advancing from Omanthai Town, according to military sources here
today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the troops moving from Nedunkerni linked up
with those north of Omanthai Town in an area close to
Puliyankulam Town yesterday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
There had been resistance from the Tamil rebels equipped with
small arms and mortars. Three rebels were killed and several
others injured while one government soldier died and 20 wounded in
the clash on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Operation Jaya Sikuru (Certain Victory) was launched by the
troops on May 13 to clear the land route from Vauniya to
Killinochchi in order to reduce heavy and expensive air transport.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels fighting for a separate state have run out of
medical supplies and lost a large number of weapons in the
operation, the sources added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
