<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Biggest Research Center on Respiratory Diseases Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- China's biggest research center
on respiratory diseases has been set up in Shanghai, a leading
base for treatment of such diseases and for taking precaution
measures against and control of tuberculoses in the country.
</P>
<P>
The research center comprises doctors and researchers from five
hospitals in the municipality -- the Zhongshan Hospital, Huashan
Hospital, Shanghai Tumor Hospital, Shanghai Pediatric Hospital,
and the No.1 Lung Disease Hospital. The hospitals are among the
most prominent for treatment of lung diseases in the country.
</P>
<P>
It is the fifth such research facility in the country, after
four others in Shenyang, Beijing, and Guangzhou cities.
</P>
<P>
Respiratory diseases are the No.1 killer in China. With the
increasing incidence of chronic and obstructive lung diseases,
asthma, lung cancer, and non-tuberculous lung infection, more
attention has been called for to enhance research on such
diseases.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
