<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0182 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Hails ASEAN's Achievements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today sent a congratulation message to Philippine President and
ASEAN Chairman Fidel Ramos to mark the 30th anniversary of the
ASEAN's founding, which falls on Friday.
</P>
<P>
In the message, Jiang highly praised the achievements by the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in the past three
decades, and hoped to further enhance China's relations with the
regional grouping and its member states.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN, which came into being on August 8, 1967, now comprises
Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines,
Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
"Marching along the road to peace and development, ASEAN has,
in the past three decades, become a very active organization in
the Asia-Pacific region with its unique influence in regional
affairs, " Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that The Southeast Asian region has maintained a sound
momentum of economic growth and has seen considerable progress in
cooperation of various forms thanks to concerted efforts by ASEAN
member states.
</P>
<P>
"We are very pleased to see ASEAN admit new members on its
thirtieth anniversary. Its enlargement and development conform to
the trend toward multipolarization in the world and conduce to a
lasting peace and development in the Asia-Pacific, " the Chinese
president said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has all along supported and will continue to
support ASEAN in its efforts to play a positive role in regional
and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese government and people are committed to
establishing a partnership of good-neighborliness and mutual trust
with ASEAN, a relationship that is geared toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
China is "satisfied to see friendly relations and cooperation
between China and ASEAN countries grow in strength. The
China-ASEAN relations are developing smoothly with the
establishment of a full dialogue partnership between the two sides
and increasingly closer consultation and cooperation between them
in regional and international affairs, " Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Cooperation between the two sides in various fields holds out
broad prospects, " he said, "The relationship between China and
ASEAN is now entering a new phase of an all-round development."
</P>
<P>
China stands ready to work with ASEAN countries to development
friendly and good-neighborly relations, expand mutually beneficial
cooperation and bring about a lasting peace and development in the
region and the world at large, Jiang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
