<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's New Municipality Attracting More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Japan's Isuzu Motors,
Thailand's Chia Tai Group, and a British multinational have
decided to spend 120 million US dollars more in Chongqing, part of
the 50 percent increase in overseas investment in the first half
of the year.
</P>
<P>
This influx is mainly attributed to Chongqing's status being to
that of a municipality, in March, China's fourth, after Beijing,
Shanghai, and Tianjin, and to its development potential with
favorable central government policies.
</P>
<P>
The new municipality covers a total of 82,000 sq km and has
more than 30 million people, and has the possibility of becoming
another popular investment spot after Shanghai's Pudong New Area,
according to economists.
</P>
<P>
Its new status has drawn the growing attention of overseas
business people. Two Japanese banks have opened offices in the
city, and other banks have begun to do feasibility studies.
</P>
<P>
"As a municipality directly under the State Council, or the
central government, Chongqing will play an increasingly important
role in China's social and economic activities. Therefore, my
group has decided to shift investment priority in China to this
interior city," said Kim Gao Choong, chief representative of
Korea's Hyundai Group in China.
</P>
<P>
The central government has granted the municipality with the
same favorable policies as Pudong, Vice-Mayor Xu Zhongmin noted.
These include: the state gives priority to overseas-funded banks,
department stores, and supermarkets in Chongqing; the city's
enterprises enjoy advantages in issuing H-shares and B-shares
overseas; the state will provide more loans to the city; and
income tax of overseas businesses will be reduced from 33 to 24
percent.
</P>
<P>
The municipality also plans to put 250 billion yuan into fixed
assets during the Ninth Five-Year period (1996-2000), and to
utilize some 3.5 to four billion US dollars in overseas capital,
an increase of over 100 percent over the previous five years.
</P>
<P>
Economists predict that living expenses for urban and rural
residents will increase by 24 billion yuan at the end of the
century, giving the municipality potential as a consumer goods
market.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing is the largest economic center in southwest China and
on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River, and is widely
considered to be a mjor force for China's two 21st century
strategies, namely, to opening up the Yangtze River valley and the
westward shift in economic development.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing straddles China's east-west juncture and is part of
the westward trend in economic development, and will try to link
the capital and technology of the east to the resources in the
west. And the Three Gorges Dam has provided still more
opportunities for overseas investment and businesses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0184 </DOCNO>
