<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Opening-Up Drive (I) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- In a review of China's opening-up
drive of the past five years, Guangming Daily today said it has
brought more overseas investment and trade opportunities and
energy and expertise into an emerging economy.
</P>
<P>
After coastal regions became the beneficiaries of the first
round of opening up, the vast interior, which contains some of
China's most backward regions, looked for its own channels to
contact the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
The Yangtze River, with Shanghai at its east end, was designed
to carry the economic growth for an area where two-thirds of
China's people live. Wuhan, a trade and transport hub in central
China, and Chongqing, China's newest and largest municipality, and
six other cities along the river, were designed as strategic
outlets of growth.
</P>
<P>
Thirteen border cities were also allowed to increase economic
ties with neighboring countries. And, the opening of inland
provincial capitals, which were mostly old industrial bases, into
bases for overseas capital, technology, and expertise.
</P>
<P>
By now, 359 Chinese cities and counties with a population of
300 million and an area of 500,000 square kilometers have opened
to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
Open coastal regions have become a major force in China's
economy, 12 of which were pioneers in last year's drive,
attracting 88 percent of the overseas investment in China. Their
combined GDP accounted for 58 percent of China's total, and their
trade volume for 89 percent.
</P>
<P>
China's five special economic zones, which were experimental
refrom areas, have all had more than 30 percent annual growth in
recent years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0186 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya to Start Anti-Polio Campaign Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan Health Ministry is
scheduled to launch the second national anti-polio campaign
tomorrow in a bid to eradicate polio in the country.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, which started last year in the country, will be
divided into two rounds this year in order to cover wider area,
according to Health Minister Jackson Mulinge.
</P>
<P>
The first round will take place on August 9 and 10 and the
second one on September 13 and 14.
</P>
<P>
A total of 89 stations have been set up at health centers,
schools, markets and other accessible places throughout the East
African country.
</P>
<P>
Mulinge said that the government had set targets to immunize
more than five million children below the age of five during the
campaign.
</P>
<P>
Kenya is one of more than 30 countries in Africa which will
participate in this year's anti-polio campaign sponsored by the
World Health Organization.
</P>
<P>
According to global statistics, as of April this year, only
about 3,400 cases of polio were reported last year in the world,
representing a 90 percent decline from the 35,000 cases reported
in 1988 when the campaign started.
</P>
<P>
The African continent has the highest polio cases in 1996 with
1,670 cases reported, accounting for 49 percent of the global
total.
</P>
<P>
However, a ray of hope exists in the African continent as
polio free zones are emerging in the southern, northern and
eastern parts of the continent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
