<HEADLINE> Jiang Congratulates ASEAN Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
sent a message of congratulations today to Philippine President
Fidel Ramos, chairman of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations, marking the 30th anniversary of ASEAN's founding.
</P>
<P>
The full text of the message reads:
</P>
<P>
On the occasion of the thirtieth anniversary of the founding of
ASEAN, I wish to extend, on behalf of the Chinese Government and
people and in my own name, our warm congratulations to Your
Excellency and, through you, to the member states of ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Marching along the road to peace and development, ASEAN has, in
the past three decades, become a very active organization in the
Asia-Pacific region with its unique influence in regional
affairs. Thanks to concerted efforts by member states of ASEAN,
the Southeast Asian region has maintained a sound momentum of
economic growth and has seen considerable progress in cooperation
of various forms. We are very pleased to see ASEAN admit new
members on its thirtieth anniversary. Its enlargement and
development conform to the trend toward multipolarization in the
world and conduce to a lasting peace and development in the
Asia-Pacific. China has all along supported and will continue to
support ASEAN in its efforts to play a positive role in regional
and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government and people are committed to establishing
a partnership of good-neighborliness and mutual trust with ASEAN,
a relationship that is geared toward the 21st century. We are
satisfied to see friendly relations and cooperation between China
and ASEAN countries grow in strength. The China-ASEAN relations
are developing smoothly with the establishment of a full dialogue
partnership between the two sides and increasingly closer
consultation and cooperation between them in regional and
international affairs. Cooperation between the two sides in
various fields holds out broad prospects. The relationship between
China and ASEAN is now entering a new phase of an all-round
development. China stands ready to work with ASEAN countries to
develop friendly and good-neighborly relations, expand mutually
beneficial co-operation and bring about a lasting peace and
development in the region and the world at large. 
</P>
</TEXT>
