<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bolivia's New President Sworn in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Hugo Banzer, who was elected
president of Bolivia in the second round of election held in
parliament Tuesday, was sworn in in La Paz today, according
to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
In his inaugural speech, Banzer said that during his five years
in office, he will make efforts to eliminate illiteracy and
poverty and promote the country's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Banzer, candidate of the Nationalist Democratic Action party,
who was Bolivia's president between 1971-1978, defeated all the
others with about 21 percent of the votes during the July 1
election.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Banzer's winning of the second round of election
paved the way for him to form a coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from 52 countries and 10 international
organizations were present at the swearing-in ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
