<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rebels Raid Uganda From Sudan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 8 (Xinhua) -- A rebel group numbering between
200 and 300 raided north-western Uganda from Sudan, The New
Vision, reported today.
</P>
<P>
Colonel James Kazini, the commander of the fourth division,
said the Uganda National Rescue Front II (UNRF II) attackers have
been repulsed to southern Sudan.
</P>
<P>
Ugandan army reinforced its deployment in Koboko and Moyo
districts after the attack and the road from Yumbe to Moyo was
blocked temporarily.
</P>
<P>
The raid occurred several days after some UNRF II political
leaders were arrested.
</P>
<P>
An earlier report said UNRF II had recruited some 1,000 Muslim
youths in Arua and Koboko districts, north-western Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The recruited youths have been sent to Juba, southern Sudan,
for training, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
