<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosion Kills One, Injures Two in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The explosion of a suspected bomb
planted roadside killed one and injured two others in Port
Harcourt, Rivers State in south Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Local media said the accident happened Wednesday on the busy
Kaduna Street at the noon, when a curious hawker was picking up a
paper bag on the roadside to see what is inside. He was killed
immediately.
</P>
<P>
Two of his colleagues also saw the package and were following
him. They were seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
The explosion was reportedly heard about half a kilometers
away and soon threw the city into panic, reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
