<HEADLINE> Pak-China Relations Is A Model of Inter-State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari said here today that relations between his country and
China have become a model of inter-state relations worthy of envy
and emulation by others.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with visiting Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan, the president appreciated the positive and useful
contributions China has made in the economic development of
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his confidence that special relations between the
two countries would be further deepened, Leghari emphasized the
need for further expansion in bilateral trade and economic
relations.
</P>
<P>
Tang Jiaxuan, who arrived here Monday evening for a two-day
visit,
conveyed to Leghari the good wishes of Chinese President Jiang
Zemin and Prime Minister Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Tang also expressed the confidence that relations between the
two countries would enjoy sustainable development in future.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today Tang called on Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif. The
two sides exchanged views on Sino-Pak relations, regional issues
and other matters of mutual interest.
</P>
<P>
Sharif briefed Tang about the Pakistan-India talks and stressed
his commitment to seek resolutions of all outstanding issues with
India through dialogue and peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that China was concerned about the Kashmir issue and
was sympathetic with the people of Kashmir and their sufferings.
</P>
<P>
Concluding his two-day visit to Pakistan, Tang left here for
Sri Lanka later this evening.  
</P>
</TEXT>
