<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Improve Telephone Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Plans to supply reliable
telephone services to all regions by installing Subscriber Trank
Dialings (STD) all over Tanzania has been completed.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Minister for Science, Technology and High
Education Jackson Makweta while answering a question on behalf of
the Minister for Communications and Transport in Parliament in
Dodoma Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Makweta said that the government has finalized plans to
install STD in all the regions through by the Tanzania
Telecommunications Company Ltd (TTCL).
</P>
<P>
Efforts are being made to extend STD to all districts so the
whole country will be provided with STD very soon to facilitate
telephone communication, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also disclosed another program known as the Integrated
Telecommunications Project financed by the World Bank to improve
telephone services in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not say when this project will be finalized.
</P>
</TEXT>
