<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Bank Supports Pillar Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shanghai, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) recently granted
902 million yuan in loans to five major state-owned enterprises in
the city.
</P>
<P>
The five enterprises were the Shanghai Electric Corp., Shanghai
Chlor-alkali Chemical Co. Ltd., Shanghai Pacific Chemical (Group)
Corp. Ltd., Shanghai Tyre and Rubber Co. and Shanghai Meishan
(Group) Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Jianqing, president of the ICBC Shanghai branch, said
that as the largest financial arm in the city, his bank should
take it as its duty to support the development of large state
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
By now, the bank has issued loans worth 7.1 billion yuan this
year, with its total outstanding loans reaching 115.3 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The bank has given priority to helping invigorate pillar
industries in Shanghai, including automobile and hi-tech sectors,
manufacturers of name-band products, large industrial projects,
major commercial undertakings and public facilities.
</P>
<P>
The bank's efforts have paid off. By the end of June this year,
the output value of 39 large state enterprises, which have
received utmost support from the bank, topped 62.6 billion yuan,
6.68 percent higher than the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
These firms also reported 81.9 billion yuan in sales volume, up
7.27 percent and 302.8 billion yuan, an increase of 11.6 percent
on a year-on-year basis.  
</P>
</TEXT>
