<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 200,000 Mobile Telephone Users in North China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The number of mobile telephone
customers in China's Tianjin municipality passed the 200,000 mark
today, putting it in the fifth place in China's mainland, after
Guangzhou, Shanghai, Beijing and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
An official with the municipal Post and Telecommunications
Bureau says that after eight years of expansion, the city's mobile
phone capacity has reached 300,000.
</P>
<P>
The mobile phone network covers all of Tianjin's urban area and
85 percent of the suburbs, and is connected with the nationwide
network.
</P>
<P>
The bureau is expanding the mobile phone network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
