<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Residents in Jiangsu Enjoy Comfortable Life </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The 70-million-population
province of Jiangsu in east China reported a per-capita GNP of
8,447 yuan by the end of last year, and this means they have
started to enjoy a comfortable life three years ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
In the early 1990s, the Central Government decided, in line
with Deng Xiaoping's ideas, that the people of the country as a
whole should be able to basically lead a comfortable life by the
end of the century.
</P>
<P>
Accordingly, the State Statistics Bureau set 16 standards for
this "comfortable life", focusing on economic uplift, material
supply, population growth, services, and the environment.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Jiangsu was able to basically reach most of the
standards. An overall assessment confirmed the success of the
province in improving the life of its residents, said the
provincial Statistics Bureau director Zhang Quanyuan.
</P>
<P>
The annual per-capita income for farmers was 3,029 yuan last
year, far more than the national average. The per-person living
space was 10.61 sq m for urban dwellers, and 28.52 sq m for rural
farmers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
