<HEADLINE> Dropouts Returning to School in Southwestern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Nanning, the capital of China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, has raised 10.33 million yuan
for "Project Hope," a national program to help students from poor
families.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, almost nine million yuan has been spent on 24 Hope
primary schools that can accommodate 8,000 children. Another 1.47
million yuan has been used to help 4,900 dropouts resume their
education, accounting for 47 percent of the total in the city.
</P>
<P>
Nanning area has suffered from poverty because of its harsh
natural conditions and the dropout problem is still serious here.
</P>
