<HEADLINE> Tanzania's Export Earnings Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania's export earnings
reached 494 billion shillings (823 million US dollars at current
exchange rate) last year, a 13 percent increase over the 431
billion shillings in the year 1995.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Minister for Industries and Trade William
Shija while presenting his ministry's 1997/98 budget estimates to
Parliament held in Dodoma Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A report from Dodoma quoted Shija as saying, "Improved export
earnings was mainly due to high volume of industrial products and
raw products whose prices were also high."
</P>
<P>
Shija said 40 percent of the exports went to the European
Union (EU) countries where Tanzania imported goods worth 763.9
billion shillings (1.27 billion US Dollars) last year as against
834.2 billion shillings in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister noted, trade with member states of the
Common Market for Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA) and the
Development Community for Southern Africa was not satisfactory
though there are signs for an increase following signing of trade
protocols.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Industries and Trade has started preparations
for a trade policy which will give direction of trade operations
in the country. The policy will stress on harmonization of the
country's requirement under free market and the globalization
network, Shija said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
