<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Booming Private High-Tech Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Private enterprises in the
science and technology sector have emerged as major contributors
to China's economic growth.
</P>
<P>
State Science and Technology Commission statistics for 1996
show that the nation's 100,000 private high-tech enterprises
employed over two million workers and had total sales of 270
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Private science and technology enterprises engaged in intensive
production account for some 70 percent of the total number of
enterprises located in 112 national or provincial new and high
technology development zones. In addition, skilled technicians
working in the private high-tech sector account for over 20
percent of the total number of employees, and high-tech products
account for well over 20 percent of total sales.
</P>
<P>
Some 450 private high-tech enterprises have annual sales of
over 100 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
Some two percent of the sector's total annual revenue is
dedicated to technical research and new product development, with
related allocations far exceeding those of most township and
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Booming township enterprises characterized China's economic
development in the 1980s, with private science and technology
enterprises emerging as the key to economic prosperity in the
1990s. Economists say the private high-tech sector will play an
even greater role in the future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
