<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
rose today for the first time in the week, encouraged by a weaker
local currency and strong overseas markets overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended seven points higher at 2359 with a
turnover of 65 million NZ dollars (41 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
