<HEADLINE> Indonesian Pulp Production to Hit 3.35 Million Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's annual pulp
production is to increase from 2.9 million tons now to 3.35
million tons in 1999, Trade and Industry Minister Tunky
Ariwibowoa is quoted as saying by reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking Wednesday after the opening ceremony of the pulp plant
of Pt. Kiani Kertas, the minister said that the country's pulp
exports would reach 1.5 million tons by the end of the current
Sixth Five-Year Development Plan (1994 to 1999).
</P>
<P>
The Pt. Kiani Kertas plant would start commercial production
next week and reach its full capacity of 472,500 tons of pulp per
annum within three months. The plant is located in Berau, East
Kalimantan Province, and dubbed the largest single-line pulp mill
in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's pulp exports were recorded at 600,000 tons in 1995
and rose to 1.1 million tons in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
