<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's VP Hails China's Great Changes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's Vice-Presidnet Joshua
Nkomo said here today that great changes have taken place in
China in the past years through its economic reform and open-door
policy.
</P>
<P>
He made the remark when meeting with the visiting delegation
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) led by Li Chengren, deputy
head of the international department of the CPC central
committee.
</P>
<P>
Nkomo, who is also vice-president and second secretary of
Zambabwe's ruling Zimbabwe African National Union-Patriotic Front
(ZANU-PF) party, said the ties between his party and the CPC has
been very good.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that the friendly relations will be strengthened
through cooperations and exchanges between the two parties.
</P>
<P>
Nkomo added Zimbabwe and China shared similar views on many
international issues.
</P>
<P>
He praised China's position on important international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li Chengren said that CPC and the Chinese government have
attached importance to the friendly relations between the two
countries and parties, and hoped the ties will be further
enhanced.
</P>
<P>
Li said that he appreciated Zimbabwe's consistent stand of
upholding the "One China" policy.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that relations between the two parities has
undergone a smooth development since they established official
ties in 1982.
</P>
<P>
The CPC official said CPC is willing to expand the ties on the
four principles of complete independence, equality, mutual
respect of each other and non-interference in the internal
affairs of other parties.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation arrived here Wednesday to start a
six-day visit to Zimbabwe.  
</P>
