<HEADLINE> Constitutional Amendment Undesirable, Ukrainian Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Any attempt to cut the presidential
power through amending the Constitution will aggravate the social
and political situations in Ukraine, a senior Ukrainian official
warned Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Presidential Administration
Office Superintendent Yevgein Kushnaryov said this sort of
attempts by some legislators may cause serious problems for the
nation.
</P>
<P>
As local press reported, the proposed amendments would
virtually eliminate the presidential veto, strip the president of
his power to dismiss the prime minister without legislative
backing.
</P>
<P>
Kushnaryov said though no one meant to question the
legislators' right to make amendments to the Constitution, it
would be wrong to ignore the clear-cut provisions on power
division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
