<HEADLINE> Concert Tumult Leaves Two Dead in Lima </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- A concert turned into a tumultuous
display by fans here Tuesday when they stormed the stage to touch
their singing idols, leaving two people dead and many others
injured, the police said today.
</P>
<P>
A police report said 90 others were still missing today after
the incident at a performance by Venezuelan singers at a household
fair.
</P>
<P>
The tumult broke out when hundreds of young people stormed the
stage and tried to touch their idols. Some of the victims
collapsed and suffered injuries and contusions. Many close to the
stage were asphyxiated by the huge crowd.
</P>
<P>
The two dead girls were identified as Rosa Quispe Navarro, 18,
and Elena Arna, 19, the police said.
</P>
<P>
About 100,000 people, most of them women under 20, reportedly
assisted in the preparations for the household fair concert. On the
night before the performance, thousands of girls queued for
entrance to the concert. 
