<HEADLINE> Indonesian Pulp Production to Hit 3.35 Million Tons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's annual pulp
production is to increase from 2.9 million tons now to 3.35
million tons in 1999, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
After the pulp plant of Pt. Kiani Kertas located in Berau, East
Kalimantan Province, began production, the country's pulp exports
will reach 1.5 million tons by the end of the current Sixth
Five-Year Development Plan (1994 to 1999), Trade and Industry
Minister Tunky Ariwibowo said Wednesday after attending the
opening ceremony of the plant.
</P>
<P>
The Pt. Kiani Kertas plant, dubbed the largest single-line pulp
mill in Southeast Asia, would start commercial production next
week and reach its full capacity of 472,500 tons of pulp per annum
within three months, reports reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's pulp exports were recorded at 600,000 tons in 1995
and rose to 1.1 million tons in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
