<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China City Bolsters Products' Image </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Wenzhou in
east China's Zhejiang Province, held a fair yesterday in Beijing
to showcase the city's quality products, in a bid to wash away
people's impression that products from Wenzhou symbolize shoddy or
fake goods, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
In the 1980s, Wenzhou was widely known because of its
low-quality commodities. And such a perception has been rooted in
many Chinese people's minds.
</P>
<P>
Since the early 1990s, Wenzhou has been endeavouring to drive
its economy on a fast track by emphasizing quality, which has
resulted in satisfying achievements in the city.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 the city hit 100 billion yuan in GDP. The number of
enterprises with sales exceeding 100 million yuan each totals more
than 40 in the city.
</P>
<P>
Years of ups and downs has taught Wenzhou that steady economic
development should rely heavily on the flourishing of brand
products and powerful enterprises, said Huang Weifeng, vice-mayor
of Wenzhou.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 categories of local best products, including
heavy-duty machines, chemicals, light machines, electronics,
motorcycles, garments and leather products are on display in the
Beijing Exhibition Hall.
</P>
<P>
The fair is scheduled to last through August 10 and is the
first of its kind the city held in Beijing to introduce its
products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
