<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0261 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of Radio Pager Customers Soars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 7 (Xinhua) -- China now has 45 million radio
pager customers and an annual business volume of more than 10
billion yuan, with the number of customers expected to reach 100
million by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent post and telecoms meeting in Hangzhou,
China had 2,100 officially-approved paging companies by the end of
last year, 18 of which are operating through satellite
transmission and can cover the country.
</P>
<P>
Although the Posts and Telecoms Ministry's paging network
doesn't quite dominate the business like it used to, it is still a
leader, with over 30 million customers.
</P>
<P>
People now pay greater attention to the quality of services and
companies are trying to compete with each other by providing more
information and better services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Central Bank Cuts Overnight Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- With the peso slowly gaining
ground against the U.S. dollar on the foreign exchange market, the
Philippine Central Bank has approved a reduction of its overnight
borrowing rate from 20 percent to 18 percent effective today.
</P>
<P>
The overnight lending rate, hiked from 22 percent to 26 percent
Monday, was also slashed to 22 percent.
</P>
<P>
The central bank took the action as the peso rapidly
appreciated from 28.704 pesos to 28.51 pesos against the dollar
Wednesday with a total volume turnover of 74.1 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Central Bank Governor Gabriel Singson said Wednesday that the
move was also prompted by concern from business groups over the
high bank lending rates.
</P>
<P>
"The concern has been shifted from the foreign exchange rate to
interest rates. We expect a drop in the Treasury Bill rates with
the cut in the overnight rates," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the peso appreciation and the concurrent rise in the
volume of trade in the Philippine Dealing System, or the currency
trading system, were achieved without intervention from the
central bank.
</P>
<P>
During the past two weeks, the peso was sold at around 29 pesos
for a dollar on the foreign exchange market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Developing China's Productive Forces-1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- People's Daily has said that
China's success with socialist construction has come from
concentrating on developing productive forces.
</P>
<P>
It quotes Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), saying that the
socialist system's main contradiction is between increasing
demands for material and cultural improvement and backward
productive forces, which will last through the initial period of
socialism and affect all of society.
</P>
<P>
The CPC's fundamental task, therefore, is to concentrate on
developing productive forces. Only in this way can solutions to
all other social problems be found.
</P>
<P>
For a long time the Chinese people have dreamed of becoming
equal, independent and prosperous members of the global community,
the paper says, but there is still a gap between China and
developed countries.
</P>
<P>
China's efforts have paid off, however, as it now feeds the
world's largest population. Its GDP in 1995 was twice 1980's, and
by the year 2000 is expected to quadruple that of 1980.
</P>
<P>
So, experience has shown that the only way out is to
concentrate on developing productive forces. This was stated
repeatedly by Deng Xiaoping, the architect of China's reforms and
opening drive, who said that the nature of socialism is the
liberation and development of productive forces, elimination of
poverty and polarization, and achieving prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Only by sticking to this can we adhere to the true socialist
system, Deng explained. In view of this, China's successes in the
reforms and opening-up drive can be attributed to the "one center
and two basic points".
</P>
<P>
The center is taking economic construction as the main
task. One of the basic points is adherence to the four cardinal
principles: adherence to Maxism, Leninism and Mao Zedong thought;
adherence to the Socialist Road; adherence to the leadership of
the CPC; and adherence to the people's democratic
dictatorship. The other is adherence to the reform and opening up
policy.
</P>
<P>
The article says that backed by "three beneficials" the Chinese
people can continue to push forward the reforms and opening-up
policy. This means that any method of development that is
beneficial to the development of socialism's productive forces,
beneficial to the socialist country's strength, and beneficial to
the improvement of the people's living conditions, can be applied.
</P>
<P>
If China sticks to these principles and the fundamental task it
can reach its final goal, the article says.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US's Insurance Giant Opens Office in South China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Cigna Corp., a US-based insurance
giant, has opened a representative office in Guangzhou, capital of
south China's Guangdong Province, today's "China Daily" reported.
</P>
<P>
It is the third office Cigna opened in China, following the
other two in Beijing and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The office plans to provide life, accident, health, commercial
property, casualty and other insurance services, expected to help
Cigna have a share of southern China's insurance market and
increase the company's business with the region.
</P>
<P>
The office will ask the Chinese government for permission of
offering risk management and employee benefits programmes.
</P>
<P>
With headquarters in Philadelphia, Cigna is one of the world's
largest insurance and health-care service organizations and has
offices in more than 50 countries.
</P>
<P>
Cigna boasts more than 100 billion US dollars of assets and 7.5
billion US dollars of its equity are owned by shareholders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
