<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- The following are highlights of
major Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
 "People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The paper said that the goal to establish the socialist
market economy set at the 14th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China five years ago was the proper move.
</P>
<P>
Implementing the market economy was risky in the beginning, but
it has resulted in more competitive enterprises, and benefited
people and businesses both.
</P>
<P>
-- According to the State Council's State Commission for
Restructuring the Economic System, China will pay greater
attention to developing co-operative share-holding enterprises in
cities to help develop productive forces.
</P>
<P>
-- A book on the views of Mao Zedong, Deng Xiaoping, and Jiang
Zemin has just been published to help build socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
-- Total early rice production in central China's Hunan
Province is expected to be 17.8 percent more than last year.
</P>
<P>
"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The paper says that the socialist market economy is correct
theory and China's economy has been growing at an average rate of
11.6 percent annually since 1992.
</P>
<P>
-- The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region has had good livestock
breeding for the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
-- Henan Province purchased 3.5 million tons of grain as part
of the state quota this year and spent nearly four billion yuan on
another three million tons of grain at market prices.
</P>
<P>
-- Since 1995, the Shandong Provincial Government has been
urging local officials to avoid mediocrity.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese Government supports religious freedom and does
not discriminate against religious believers, according to a
seminar in Beijing, and religious believers now enjoy the most
favorable climate in the history of this country.
</P>
<P>
-- Beijing's Association of Relations Across the Taiwan
Straits, China's semi-official body dealing with Taiwan affairs,
will continue to promote cross-Straits exchanges and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
-- Yu Lu, a six-year-old Beijing girl earned praise for her
acting as a grandmother in a Peking Opera performance Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
-- Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong branch's new chief Jiang Enzhu
says the organization will not interfere in Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region affairs.
</P>
<P>
-- The nearly 1,700-year-old Dunhuang Grottoes are entering the
high-tech age by being protected by laser technology and infrared
photography.
</P>
<P>
 "Liberation Army Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Yu Yongbo, director of the General Political Department of
the PLA, has called on the military to study President Jiang
Zemin's May 29 speech, which laid the ideological and theoretical
basis for the 15th National Congress of the Chinese Communist
Party, and to contribute to the Congress. 
</P>
</TEXT>
