<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 40 Killed in Clash in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 7 (Xinhua) -- At least 40 persons, including
women and children, have been killed and 17 others wounded in a
recent fierce gun battle between two feuding groups in Sulu, the
southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Four teenage girls were also taken hostage by the attackers who
shot with machine guns and burned down a village last Sunday, the
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Some of the survivors have been taken to the Zamboanga City
Medical Center aboard motorized pump-boats, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The fighting between the two armed groups reportedly stemmed
from a failed parental marriage engagement in which the woman was
said to have eloped with another man.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970807.0274 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seles Survives a Hard Test in Second Round </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles of the United
States struggled in a hard fought against Sandrine Testud of
France to clinch a 6-7 (6-8), 7-6 (7-4), 6-3 victory in the second
round Wednesday at the Acura Classic in Manhattan Beach,
California.
</P>
<P>
Seles, who ranked No. 2 in the world, outlasted Testud in the
tow hours and 23 minutes marathon match after going down in a
thrilling first set.
</P>
<P>
Testud was leading the second set at 5-3 when Seles started her
comeback.
</P>
<P>
In other matches Wednesday, 1994 champion Amy Frazier of United
States downed Amanda Coetzer of South Africa 6-1, 6-3; defending
champion Lindsay Davenport defeated Yayuk Basuki of Indonesia 6-1,
6-1 in 48 minutes; and Natasha Zvereva of Belarus upset Ruxandra
Dragomir of Romania 6-2, 4-6, 7-6 (7-4).
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Martina Hingis, who owns a 54-1 record this year,
played Anne-Gaelle Sidot of France in a night match on Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
