<HEADLINE> Nicaragua's Exports Rise in January-July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua's exports hit 529
million U.S. dollars in the January-July period this year, a 19
percent rise over the same period last year, a latest Central Bank
report said.
</P>
<P>
The report showed that non-traditional goods accounted for 277
million dollars and the remaining 252 million dollars were earned
by traditional goods.
</P>
<P>
Coffee, sugar, molasses and bananas were among the fastest
growing exports. 
</P>
