<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Useful Chinese Information Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- An information network with
nearly 100 databases in Chinese language opened here this
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
By using the system, ChinaInfo, the public will get into the
Internet and get information about China's economic and social
development.
</P>
<P>
ChinaInfo is one of key projects of State Science and
Technology Commission during the 1996-2000 period and is created
by the China Science and Technology Information Institute and
Wangfang Database Corp. Information in the network is involved in
11 topics like science and technology, policies and regulations.
</P>
<P>
Headquartered in Beijing, the network has sub-systems in 30
municipalities, provinces and regions nationwide, to bring local
scientific, technological and economic information into the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
Now about 90 percent of the information in the Internet is in
English and most of the limited information in Chinese has been
entered by overseas companies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
