<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scots Beats Spaniards at World Cup Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 6 (Xinhua) -- Scotland outplayed Spain 3-0 in
group B of the women's hockey World Cup qualifying tournament here
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Having survived Spanish pressure, Sue Fraser's goal from a
penalty corner gave Scotland a 1-0 lead in the 19th minutes into
the game. Spaniards seemed dominated the first half with three
penalty corners in the opening quarter, but never scored.
</P>
<P>
Maider Telleria's 12th-minute equaliser in the second half
received strong protest of Scots and was nullified by English
umpior Margaret Hunnaball.
</P>
<P>
Followed a string of penalty corners never found the net, and
Sue MacDonald scored twice in the 63th and 65th minute
respectively to insure Scotland's victory.
</P>
<P>
Scotland now moved up to the second in the group B with the
same 7 points as leader Russia, followed by China and fourth New
Zealand, both having 5 points in the table. Zimbabwe has lost all
three matched and scored none. 
</P>
</TEXT>
