<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Success In Treating Taihu Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 7 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
has achieved initial success in treating waste pollution in Taihu
Lake, one of China's largest lakes, "China Environmental News"
reports.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Hangzhou, Jiaxing, and Huzhou established a joint
committee to oversee the related efforts.
</P>
<P>
Joint efforts have led to the closure of 170 polluting
enterprises in the region, and have reduced emissions by an
estimated 15,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Huzhou allocated 25 million yuan (about 3.2 million million US
dollars) to renovate 12 key enterprises responsible for pollution.
</P>
<P>
Jiaxing built a new wastewater treatment plant at a cost of 30
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The province has introduced an environmental protection plan
based on reducing the volume of nitrogen and phosphorus flowing into
the lake.
</P>
<P>
In addition, some 34 modern agricultural parks, ecological
villages and townships, and four-valley improvement project are
being constructed in a 52.5 sq. km. area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
