<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tiozzo Challenges Miller's Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, August 6 (Xinhua) -- WBA cruiserweight boxing titlist
Nate Miller of the United States will have a bout with French
challenger Fabrice Tiozzo on September 26 in Lyon, France,
Tiozzo's manager Jean-Marc Perono announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year-old Tiozzo, former WBC light-heavyweight champion,
has a boasting match record of 33 wins against only one loss in
his pro career, while it is 30-4 for Miller.
</P>
<P>
Tiozzo's promoter Don King, former promoter of Mike Tyson,
canceled a bout between the Frenchman and Marcelo Dominguez of
Argentina for the WBC version of the world title last month.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
