<HEADLINE> Six Killed, Ten Injured in Terrorist Action </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and 10
others injured on Wednesday evening in terrorist action in eastern
Pakistan, a report of the Associated Press of Pakistan said.
</P>
<P>
The report said that five terrorists riding on two motorbikes
fired indiscriminately at people at prayer in a mosque in Lahore,
capital city of Punjab Province, from various directions for about
five minutes.
</P>
<P>
About 150 people were offering prayers in the mosque when the
terrorists struck, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Those injured have been taken to local hospitals, said the
report.  
</P>
</TEXT>
